HEADWORD: Ctenophora
<hw>Cte*noph"o*ra</hw> <pr>(t?-n?f"?-r?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., from Gr. <?/<?/<?/, <?/<?/<?/, comb + <?/<?/<?/<?/ to
carry.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A phylum of invertebrates,
commonly ellipsoidal in shape, swimming by means of eight longitudinal
rows of paddles. They are commonly called the <altname>comb
jellies</altname>, because the separate paddles somewhat resemble combs.
This phylum was formerly classified as a subdivision (class) within the
<phylum>C⟦oe⟧lenterata</phylum>.</def>⟦br⟧
